  "worklog": "## 2026-03-29 23:38 UTC \u2014 Pillar 2: Edge Development \u2014 Copy Boost Threshold Analysis\n\n**Task:** Assess impact of SELL-side fix on copy conviction boost threshold.\n\n**Finding:** The copy boost threshold (>=100 confidence) is now nearly unreachable:\n- Old code: 11 BUY-only signals \u2192 0/11 UP = 100% confidence (trivially achieved)\n- New code: 50 total signals \u2192 needs 50/50 same direction for 100% (impossible in practice)\n- Current session: 8 UP / 42 DOWN = 68% confidence \u2192 boost does NOT fire\n\n**Impact:** Today's WIN at 11:02 relied on copy boost (bullish@100 \u2192 conv 3\u21924). Without the boost, that trade wouldn't have fired (needed conv >= 3). The SELL-side fix may prevent similar winning trades from executing Monday.\n\n**Decision:** Do NOT lower threshold yet. Collect Monday data at new calibration. If we see conf 60-80% on trades that would have won, lower threshold to 80 on Tuesday. Logging already captures conf levels.\n\n**Risk:** If threshold is too high, bot takes fewer trades (lower volume but same WR). If too low, bot takes noisy trades (higher volume but lower WR). Current priority: collect data first, then adjust.\n\n---\n\n## 2026-03-29 23:08 UTC \u2014 Pillar 1: Copy Intelligence \u2014 SELL Signal Fix\n\n**Task:** Investigate signal count discrepancy between integrator (11 signals) and raw data (50 signals).\n\n**Root cause:** Integrator only counted BUY side signals, completely ignoring 39 SELL signals. SELL Up = bearish (dumping up tokens), SELL Down = bullish. This is critical directional information that was being discarded.\n\n**Fix:** Added SELL-side counting \u2014 SELL Up/Yes increments down_count, SELL Down/No increments up_count. Now reads all 50 signals.\n\n**Before fix:** bearish@100% confidence (based on 11/50 signals \u2014 overconfident)\n**After fix:** bearish@68% confidence (based on 50/50 signals \u2014 properly calibrated)\n\n**Impact:** The copy conviction boost fires at confidence >= 100. With properly calibrated confidence, it will be much more selective \u2014 only boosting when there's overwhelming consensus, not just when we're reading a tiny sample. This prevents false conviction boosts.\n\n---\n\n## 2026-03-29 22:42 UTC \u2014 Pillar 3: End-of-Day Report\n\n**Task:** Write comprehensive daily P&L report for Sunday March 29.\n\n**Summary:** 1 trade, 1 win, +$10.36. Total capital $1,321.36. But Sunday was a BUILD day \u2014 4 strategy deployments, 2 bug fixes, W14 projection showing 82% WR / $53/day potential. W13 closed at +$216.35 (101 trades, 55% WR). V3.1+V3.2+V3.3 should transform W14.\n\n---\n\n## 2026-03-29 22:08 UTC \u2014 Pillar 2: Edge Development \u2014 Sub-Hour Timing Analysis\n\n**Task:** Find sub-hour sweet spots within V3 active hours using 40 weekday YES trades.\n\n**Key Findings:**\n\n1. **First 30 min beats second 30 min:** 86% WR (18W/3L) vs 79% (15W/4L). The edge degrades as the hour progresses.\n\n2. **Hour 12h is the gold mine:** 14W/2L (88% WR) across the full hour. Only weakness: :20-29 bucket (1W/2L, 33%). All other 10-min buckets are 100% WR.\n\n3. **Hour 19h degrades after :30",
